==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[jibe]]

===Etymology===
From obsolete Dutch ''gijben''.

===Verb===
'''gybe'''  <!-- {{en-infl-reg-other-e|gyb|e}} inflected forms not attested with this spelling-->

# {{nautical}} To change [[tack]] with the [[wind]] crossing behind the boat. (Mostly used of boats and other small sailing craft — the corresponding manuver in a sailing ship is to [[wear]].)
# {{nautical}} To shift a fore-and-aft sail suddenly and forcefully from one side to the other, while sailing before the wind. (also [[jibe]].)

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# The act of gybing.
# A sudden shift of a sail's angle, or a sudden change in the direction that a boat is sailing.
# A sudden change in direction or approach; [[vacillation]].
# A sneer. (see [[gibe]].)